{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"In 2025, ANC1 declined from ~23,600 to ~17,800 before rebounding to ~19,200 by September. 

ANC4 rose steadily to ~12,000 in April 2025, suggesting improved retention, but then fell slightly to ~10,000 by September. 

ANC1 is consistently double ANC4 indicating significant drop-out in follow-up care. Addressing gaps between first and fourth visits remains critical to ensure continuity of care and improved antenatal outcomes.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"74227775-eb14-4cef-8caf-40174baf9e05","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in antenatal care","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Following stagnation in the post-Ebola years, Penta1 utilization picked up during COVID and accelerated rapidly under IFISH Accelerated Implementation.

If this trajectory continues, the number of Penta1 vaccinations given in 2030 is projected to reach 265,000—an increase of 10% from the 2025 baseline of approximately 250,000.

By contrast, a disruption on the scale of the 2022 BCG stockout would reduce annual Penta1 vaccinations to just 150,000."},{"type":"image","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"1fed8929-2500-4079-81f0-1ab4a8a0f163","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false},"imgFile":"utilization_scenarios_PENTA1.png","imgStretch":false,"imgFit":"inside"}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Sustained momentum could deliver 265,000 Penta1 doses in 2030; disruption could cut this to 150,000"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"markdown":"Analysis of Penta1 vaccine coverage trends suggests that coverage has increased slightly in 2025.

