{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":3,"markdown":"Most indicators achieve >95% completeness at the national level, indicating that facilities are consistently submitting monthly data across all indicators.

Most counties report near-complete data across indicators, with only minimal gaps observed.

Montserrado and Margibi show some gaps in completeness, pointing to areas for targeted improvement."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.7,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"c20f1672-edfc-4140-ae2c-09a30b50443a","moduleId":"m001","selectedReplicantValue":""}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Reporting completeness"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Antenatal care first visit: In early 2025, volumes declined compared to late 2024 peaks, though no major disruptions were flagged.

Antenatal care fourth visit: ANC4 showed notable surpluses in 2025, peaking at +19.1% in Jul (~1,700 additional visits nationally) and remaining 13% above expected in Sep.

As 2025 begins, ANC1 shows an overall downward shift compared to late 2024 while ANC4 exceeds expectations, underscoring the need to closely monitor whether changes in the health sector affect early contact and continuity of care differently."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"40deda13-d17b-458c-9e66-60325cb6e546","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Overall, ANC1 remained aligned with expected trends, while ANC4 showed surpluses in 2025"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"On the IFISH Accelerated Implementation trajectory, institutional deliveries by skilled birth attendants would grow by more than 55% from 2025 to 2030, reaching about 248,000 deliveries in 2030 alone.

