{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"OPD new cases >5 years: After some disruptions in 2023, volumes were aligned with expected values in 2024, reaching a clear surplus in 2025 (~13% above expected).

OPD new cases <5 years: After modest disruptions in 2023, surpluses emerged in late 2024 and 2025 (~21% above expected).

OPD visits are stabilizing, with both age groups showing recovery by 2025. "},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"30608f3a-f447-4445-be1a-44e1cd8bb73c","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"OPD visits rose above expected levels in 2025, with a stronger rebound among individuals aged 5+ than among children under five"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"Vaccine service volumes and children <1 fully immunized dipped through mid-2023–24, then rebounded in 2025.

 In 2025, vaccination doses were ~17–24,000/month for BCG, 17–26,000 for Penta1, ~16–24,000 for Penta3, and ~16-19,000 children <1 fully immunized. In 2025, Penta3 remained ~8% below Penta1 on average, indicating follow-up remains a priority area.

Encouragingly, all vaccines show upwards trends overall in 2025, suggesting recent improvements in both uptake and retention, though further strengthening of follow-up strategies is still needed.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"2ac2c219-a279-48a3-b9d1-ed7d8c6683f6","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in child immunization","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":3,"markdown":"Most indicators achieve >95% completeness at the national level, indicating that facilities are consistently submitting monthly data across all indicators.

Most counties report near-complete data across indicators, with only minimal gaps observed.

Grand Gedeh, Margibi, Montserrado, and River Gee show some gaps in completeness, pointing to areas for targeted improvement."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.6,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"7ed21112-419a-4332-af83-e04c54e8b408","moduleId":"m001","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Reporting completeness"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Malaria rapid diagnostic tests positive (RDT+): Volumes fell well below expectations in 2022–2023, then showed surpluses in 2023–2024, likely linked to outbreaks. In early 2025, they remain 5.5% below expected (≈ 8,900 fewer cases).

Treatment <24 hrs: Mirrors RDT+, with shortfalls in 2022–2023, partial recovery in 2024, and early 2025 still 10.9% below expected (≈ 13,700 fewer cases).

Even after adjusting for seasonality, malaria services show prolonged disruptions followed by volatile rebounds, with 2025 shortfalls signaling ongoing challenges in malaria service delivery."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"2cdad879-38a5-4983-8caa-197a8430be18","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Malaria testing and treatment remain below expected levels in early 2025, with shortfalls persisting beyond seasonal patterns"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","titleTextRelFontSize":10,"subTitleText":"","subTitleTextRelFontSize":6,"presenterText":"","presenterTextRelFontSize":4,"dateText":"","dateTextRelFontSize":3,"logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","sectionTextRelFontSize":8,"smallerSectionText":"","smallerSectionTextRelFontSize":5},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"A 20% reduction in coverage of key interventions would result in ~14% more maternal deaths and ~13% more child deaths.

At the extreme, a 50% reduction in coverage of key interventions  could lead to 34% more maternal deaths and 33% more child deaths in 2025.

These scenarios show the sensitivity of outcomes to the magnitude of service disruptions, underlining how even moderate reductions can produce large mortality impacts.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"image","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"imgFile":"fig_2_18Mar2025.png"}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"The scale of service disruption matters—greater reductions drive disproportionate mortality impacts"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"Client counselled for FP was stable without any notable variations in from Q3 2023 to Q3 2025.

Clients initiated on modern contraceptive methods and adolescent modern contraceptive users had more frequent fluctuation, with >10% surges in Q2 and Q3 2024, and growth again in Q3 2025; both declined in Q1 2025.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"c4a1b7b7-fa63-4ef4-879c-d949e1ce4cb4","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Quarter-to-quarter change in service volume
