{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"Institutional deliveries and postnatal care visits followed similar upward trends through mid-2025, peaking at roughly 15,700 and 14,400 respectively in May before declining in subsequent months. 

The difference between institutional deliveries and PNC visits within 24 or 48 hours after delivery indicates a potential gap in continuum of care.

Caesarean section volumes remained relatively low and stable throughout the period, with only minor fluctuations in early 2025.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"46e85e55-59ae-4451-a283-a9025c783278","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in deliveries and postnatal care services","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"OPD new cases >5 years show notable fluctuations but an upward trend overall, rising from  a low of ~131,000 per month in late-2023 to a high of over 190,000 per month by mid-2025 before falling to ~170,000 by Sep. 


OPD new cases <5 years remain comparatively stable, between 46,500–72,000 monthly, with smaller peaks in early and mid-2025.

The contrast suggests that while adult OPD demand is growing significantly, child OPD demand remains steady, pointing to different drivers of service utilization by age group.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"b9301546-fffa-4349-90b9-bc9ff7a552fa","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Trends in outpatient visits","useFooter":false,"footerText":""}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"markdown":"Analysis of Penta3 vaccine coverage trends suggests that coverage has recovered since its low point in 2019 but has largely stalled in recent years.

Analysis of HMIS service utilization data alone suggests that Penta3 coverage increased from a low of 74% in 2021 to a high of 83% in 2024.","span":5},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.6,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"4922243c-d4d9-4add-9736-3aa44b457326","moduleId":"m004","selectedReplicantValue":"penta3","replicateBy":"indicator_common_id","isDefault":false},"hideFigureFootnote":true}],[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"markdown":"Extrapolating HMIS trends to the most recent survey/modelled estimate, Penta3 coverage in 2025 is 82%. 

Sub-nationally in 2025, coverage ranged from 57% to 97% across counties.","span":5},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.4,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"e6d432b5-feab-4bc8-93ab-c402eea324e3","moduleId":"m004","replicateBy":"indicator_common_id","selectedReplicantValue":"penta3","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Estimating Penta3 service coverage"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"image","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgFile":"20033631845_83350bddf9_o.jpg","imgFit":"cover","markdown":""},{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"primary","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"markdown":"The FASTR approach uses routine HMIS data to monitor how service delivery shifts over time.

By comparing observed vs. expected service volumes — adjusted for seasonality and historical trends — we can identify disruptions or surpluses in key health services.

This analysis provides a timely, system-wide perspective, highlighting where and when service use deviates from expected patterns. Findings generate actionable evidence to guide rapid responses, helping sustain continuity of essential care during funding uncertainty or operational change."}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Tracking Disruptions in Essential Services Using HMIS Data","useFooter":false,"footerLogos":[]}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"OPD new cases >5 years: After some disruptions in 2023, volumes were aligned with expected values in 2024, reaching a clear surplus in 2025 (~13% above expected).

OPD new cases <5 years: After modest disruptions in 2023, surpluses emerged in late 2024 and 2025 (~21% above expected).

OPD visits are stabilizing, with both age groups showing recovery by 2025. "},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"30608f3a-f447-4445-be1a-44e1cd8bb73c","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"OPD visits rose above expected levels in 2025, with a stronger rebound among individuals aged 5+ than among children under five"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","span":3,"markdown":"ANC1 experienced a drop of 13% in Q2 2024 followed by a rebound of 13% in Q4. ANC4 volumes were more stable through 2024, followed by large increases in service volume in Q1 and Q2 2025. 

The gap between ANC1 and ANC4 services highlights the critical importance of retention strategies to ensure pregnant women complete all recommended visits.","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false},{"type":"figure","presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"546a7920-2064-4d3c-af18-a85771cf4736","moduleId":"m003","isDefault":false,"selectedReplicantValue":""},"stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"placeholderStretch":true,"placeholderHeight":50,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"imgHeight":300,"imgFit":"inside","imgStretch":true,"hideFigureCaption":false,"hideFigureSubCaption":false,"hideFigureFootnote":false}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Quarter-to-quarter change in service volume 
