{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Diarrhea and pneumonia cases have remained well below expected levels since late 2023, with prolonged disruptions through 2024.

In early 2025, some rebound is visible, especially for pneumonia, but volumes are still 15.9% lower for diarrhea (~13,300 fewer cases) and 22.8% lower for pneumonia (~22,300 fewer cases) compared to expectations.

The parallel declines across both indicators suggest broader child health service or reporting gaps, raising concerns that children may not be accessing the care they need rather than isolated fluctuations."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"d7d1c155-d4cd-47ef-8dda-ceea90abf28e","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Child illness cases have remained below expected levels since 2023, with only partial rebound in 2025"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Trends for adolescent counseling for FP were volatile, with repeated declines below expected levels, including a disruption in September 2025 (~11% decline).

Adolescents initiated on modern contraceptive methods and adolescent modern contraceptive users had more frequent fluctuation and followed similar trends, with average disruptions of ~30% for initiations and ~31% for modern-method users, respectively, improving slightly in Jul–Sep 2025.

Adolescent family planning indicators reflect irregular patterns and instability, pointing to challenges in ensuring consistent adolescent reproductive health services."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.7,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"1fed8929-2500-4079-81f0-1ab4a8a0f163","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Adolescent family planning indicators show fluctuations, but overall trends remain flat through 2025, suggesting no major systemic change"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"After declining in the post-Ebola period, Penta3 utilization rebounded during COVID-19 and accelerated further under the IFISH Accelerated Implementation.

Looking ahead, the current IFISH trajectory projects that vaccinations will reach 263,000 doses by 2030.

In contrast, a major shock event, like the 2022 BCG stockout, could slash the 2030 volume to only 135,000 doses."},{"type":"image","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"40deda13-d17b-458c-9e66-60325cb6e546","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false},"imgFile":"utilization_scenarios_PENTA3.png","imgStretch":true,"imgFit":"inside"}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Sustained IFISH Accelerated Implementation gains could deliver 263,000 Penta3 doses in 2030"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Antenatal care first visit: In early 2025, volumes declined compared to late 2024 peaks, though no major disruptions were flagged.

Antenatal care fourth visit: ANC4 showed notable surpluses in 2025, peaking at +19.1% in Jul (~1,700 additional visits nationally) and remaining 13% above expected in Sep.

As 2025 begins, ANC1 shows an overall downward shift compared to late 2024 while ANC4 exceeds expectations, underscoring the need to closely monitor whether changes in the health sector affect early contact and continuity of care differently."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"40deda13-d17b-458c-9e66-60325cb6e546","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Overall, ANC1 remained aligned with expected trends, while ANC4 showed surpluses in 2025"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"Deliveries: Stable through 2023–24, followed by a clear surplus in early 2025, with ~1,200 more facility deliveries than expected per month (+9.6%), followed by a moderate decline mid-2025, though still near expected levels by September.

PNC visits: Multiple disruptions below expected levels in 2023–24, followed by an an increase and subsequent decrease in 2025 that brought volumes closer to expected trends. 

Because PNC typically follows delivery trends, we would expect these indicators to move together, and in 2025, we see both indicators following the same trends, with institutional deliveries reaching a surplus."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"5a53efc1-d170-4285-bf1e-4d9b37cba5d9","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Deliveries show surplus in 2025, while PNC recovered after earlier disruptions"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":0.8,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":3,"markdown":"On average, fewer than 1% of facility-months across counties are flagged as outliers, showing that unusually high values are very uncommon in Liberia’s HMIS data.

Most indicators and counties show <1% outliers, with isolated deviations in indicators related to family planning (e.g., adolescents counselled for family planning, family planning clients counseled, clients initiated on modern contraceptive method, and modern contraceptive users).

Some counties (i.e., Bomi, Bong, Grand Bassa, Lofa, Nimba, Rivercess, and Sinoe) show a pattern of outliers for family planning, with 2 or more indicators reporting outside expected ranges."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.6,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"c100afed-010a-4271-8584-e6a142985a45","moduleId":"m001","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Outliers"}}

{"type":"freeform","cover":{"titleText":"","subTitleText":"","presenterText":"","dateText":"","logos":[]},"section":{"sectionText":"","smallerSectionText":""},"freeform":{"content":[[{"type":"text","stretch":true,"fillArea":true,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"grey","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":false,"figureAdditionalScale":1,"span":4,"markdown":"BCG: Sustained disruptions through 2024, with volumes dipping below expectations with an average disruption of ~14% from May to December 2024, but steady recovery into mid-2025 with sustained periods of surplus followed by one small dip in August 2025 of 12%.

Penta1 & Penta3: Also showed shortfalls in 2024, followed by a clear rebound in 2025, with large surpluses from June to September (+16% and +15% on average), with signs of strengthening service continuity.

The parallel recovery across BCG, Penta1, and Penta3 suggests a real system-wide rebound in immunization, not just random fluctuation."},{"type":"figure","stretch":true,"fillArea":false,"textSize":1,"textBackground":"none","placeholderInvisible":false,"useFigureAdditionalScale":true,"figureAdditionalScale":0.8,"presentationObjectInReportInfo":{"id":"2ac52493-e791-4f7f-9c28-fe5a3520d216","moduleId":"m003","selectedReplicantValue":"","isDefault":false}}]],"useHeader":true,"headerText":"Despite widespread shortfalls in 2024, immunization services show signs of recovery by mid-2025, with some disruption in BCG"}}
